    "points": [
      "MQTT (Message Queuing Telemetry Transport) is a lightweight messaging protocol",
      "It is widely used in IoT applications due to its efficiency and scalability"
    ],
    "script": "MQTT is designed for low-bandwidth, low-latency communication. It uses a publish-subscribe model to allow devices to communicate with each other without the need for explicit connections."
  },
