    "id": 2,
    "title": "MQTT Message Structure",
    "points": [
      "MQTT messages consist of a header and a payload",
      "The header contains the message topic, QoS (Quality of Service), and retention time"
    ],
    "script": "In MQTT, each message has three main parts: header, payload, and optional fields. The header specifies the topic and QoS, while the payload is the actual data being sent."
  },
