    "id": 3,
    "title": "QoS in MQTT",
    "points": [
      "MQTT Quality of Service (QoS) determines the level of reliability required",
      "QoS 0: At most once, best effort; QoS 1: At least once, guaranteed delivery; QoS 2: Exactly once"
    ],
    "script": "In MQTT, QoS is used to specify the level of reliability needed for message delivery. The three levels are QoS 0 (at most once), QoS 1 (at least once), and QoS 2 (exact once)"
  },
